s-drive-institutions-to-secondary-market", "title": "Private Asset Illiquidity Drives Institutions to Secondary Market - Markets Media", "content": "\\u201cSecondary market transactions, traditionally a tool for investors in distress, have become more mainstream in the institutional space,\\u201d says James Tamposi, associate director. \\u201cThe pricing discounts have continued to shrink, allowing secondary sellers to take less of a haircut when they need access to liquidity or simply adjust exposures. As the secondary market becomes more of a tool for portfolio management, asset owners have more flexibility to reshape their private market exposures and", "score": 0.29413435, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.wallstreetprep.com/knowledge/illiquidity-discount", "title": "Illiquidity Discount | Formula + Calculator", "content": "The illiquidity discount is the discount applied to the valuation of an asset, as compensation for the reduced marketability.\\n\\nIn other words, upon purchasing the investment, there is an immediate risk of value loss where the asset cannot be sold again \\u2013 i.e. the cost of buyer\\u2019s remorse in which it is difficult to reverse the purchase.\\n\\nThe illiquidity discount stems from liquidity risk, which is the incurred loss in asset value from the inability to easily liquidate the position.", "score": 0.2940279, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://verdadcap.com/archive/the-illiquidity-premium", "title": "The Illiquidity Premium \\u2014 Verdad", "content": "outperformed public equities somewhere between 1.7% per year and 3.8% per year. Beauty in private markets is in the eye of the beholder, specifically in the extent to which LPs incorporate a mark-to-market discount that reflects pricing in the secondary markets or on the London exchange. Most allocators with substantial private equity allocations likely underwrote greater outperformance than these trailing numbers would suggest, particularly when incorporating an illiquidity discount.", "score": 0.29040748, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://lotusamity.medium.com/estimating-an-illiquidity-discount-using-option-modelling-b72beaefd244", "title": "Estimating an illiquidity discount using option modelling", "content": "in the share price. An option model provides a relatively simple method to estimate an illiquidity discount taking into account the price volatility and the time from listing to close.", "score": 0.26439917, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://bondadviser.com.au/news-and-insights/credit-research/bonds/why-causes-bond-market-illiquidity", "title": "What Causes Bond Market Illiquidity? - Bond Adviser", "content": "which profit on the difference between the bid (buying) and ask (selling) prices or the \\u201cbid-ask spread\\u201d.  This spread, as well as representing a profit margin, also captures illiquidity costs, with a higher spread inferring less ability for parties to converge on a given price driven by lack of transparency and higher information asymmetry, and hence, greater illiquidity. Due to a combination of the above (and other structural factors), the Australian bond market lacks the level of depth and", "score": 0.2631617, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.texture.capital/insights/the-illiquidity-discount", "title": "The Illiquidity Discount \\u2013 Costing Issuers Tens of Billions of Dollars per Year \\u2014 Texture", "content": "been extensively researched in the context of private company valuation. In this field it is referred to as the Discount for Lack of Marketability reflecting the fact that for private investments there is often no liquid secondary market with restrictions of resale of securities identified as a key factor. Indeed, the IRS has published on their website a one hundred- and sixteen-page document on measuring the discount for lack of marketability and includes a summary of some of the studies shown", "score": 0.24659275, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.wallstreetmojo.com/illiquidity-discount", "title": "Illiquidity Discount - Definition, Examples, How To Estimate?", "content": "their illiquid nature. In such cases, a discount on the illiquid asset\'s value is warranted, as it likely attracts buyers. Various methods are employed to compute illiquidity discounts for private companies\' assets, including the trading volume and bid-ask spread, market-based methods, and stochastic discount factor models. Therefore, each asset follows a different method through which its illiquidity discount is calculated.  Direct approach: Deduct the illiquidity discount from the asset\'s", "score": 0.24178061, "raw_content": null}]',
